                                        <h2>College Of Social Work and Communnity Development</h2>
                                        <p>The College of Social Work and Community Development envisions a society where social justice, equality, and inclusivity prevail, and communities thrive in harmony and empowerment. We aim to be a pioneering institution in social work education, research, and advocacy, dedicated to producing compassionate and competent social workers and community developers. Our vision is to inspire a new generation of professionals who champion human rights, social welfare, and community well-being, driving positive change and fostering resilient communities.</p>
                                        <p>Our mission at the College of Social Work and Community Development is to provide transformative education, research, and outreach programs that equip students with the knowledge, skills, and ethical values to address social challenges and promote community development. We are committed to fostering a deep understanding of social theories, human behavior, community dynamics, and social policy. Through rigorous academic curricula, fieldwork experiences, and community engagement initiatives, we prepare our students to become empathetic and effective social workers and community developers.</p>
